Fi.insider.com%2F650316811afe8f0019ea6717%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-on-the-galpagos-islands-according-to-frequent-visitor%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Things%20to%20do%20on%20the%20Gal%C3%A1pagos%20Islands%20include%20spending%20time%20with%20local%20wildlife%20and%20hiking%20to%20the%20rim%20of%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20volcanic%20craters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Marci%20Vaughn%20Kolt%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A75%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-on-the-galpagos-islands-according-to-frequent-visitor%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Retinol%20vs.%20Retin-A%20vs.%20Retinoid%3A%20Differences%2C%20benefits%2C%20side%20effects%2C%20and%20expert%20recommended%20products%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20model%20with%20a%20swipe%20of%20the%20ALASTIN%20Renewal%20Retinol%20on%20their%20cheekbone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792bf6f10c98eace913bda4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221350%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EALASTIN%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20new%20to%20the%20wonderful%20world%20of%20retinoids%2C%20you%20may%20have%20noticed%20they%20come%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20strengths%20and%20formulations.%20You%20also%20may%20have%20wondered%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fwhat-does-retinol-do%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhat%20does%20retinol%20do%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20my%20skin%3F%20Retinoids%20can%20be%20used%20to%20treat%20everything%20from%20wrinkles%20and%20sun%20spots%20to%20acne%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.som.md%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Saami%20Khalifian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20double%20board-certified%20dermatologist%20and%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.som.md%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESOM%20Aesthetics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20well-studied%20and%20known%20to%20stimulate%20cellular%20turnover%2C%20boost%20collagen%20production%2C%20and%20regulate%20oil%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20Khalifian%20tells%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Khalifian%2C%20understanding%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20different%20types%20of%20retinoids%20is%20key%20in%20determining%20which%20one%20best%20meets%20your%20needs.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20may%20have%20wondered%20whether%20retinol%20or%20Retin-A%20is%20right%20for%20you.%20While%20there%20is%20some%20crossover%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20benefits%20you%20can%20expect%20with%20all%20retinoids%2C%20they%20do%20vary%20quite%20a%20bit%20in%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20here's%20everything%20dermatologists%20want%20you%20to%20know%20about%20the%20differences%20between%20Retin-A%2C%20retinol%2C%20and%20retinoids%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b15cc36-7c46-42d6-a1e7-78ca24a77eda%5C%22%3EWhat%20are%20retinoids%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetinoids%20are%20a%20class%20of%20chemicals%20derived%20from%20vitamin%20A.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrannachacon.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnna%20Chacon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MD%2C%20a%20board-certified%20dermatologist%20in%20private%20practice%2C%20retinoids%20can%20help%20to%20improve%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWrinkles%20and%20fine%20lines%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAcne%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fhyperpigmentation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHyperpigmentation%3C%2Fa%3E%20(dark%20spots)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUneven%20tone%20or%20texture%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretinol-can-reduce-large-pores-and-textured-skin-dermatologist-advice-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnlarged%20pores%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20accomplish%20this%20partly%20by%20increasing%20your%20cell's%20turnover%20rate%20and%20boosting%20collagen%20production%2C%20explains%20Chacon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetinoids%20come%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20strengths%20and%20formulations%2C%20including%20retinol%2C%20retinaldehyde%20(retinal)%2C%20and%20retinoic%20acid%20(tretinoin)%20%E2%80%94%20commonly%20known%20by%20the%20brand%20name%20Retin-A.%20Some%20forms%20can%20be%20found%20over-the-counter%2C%20while%20other%20more%20potent%20forms%20require%20a%20prescription%20due%20to%20the%20higher%20concentration%20of%20active%20ingredients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20retinoids%20ultimately%20get%20converted%20into%20retinoic%20acid%2C%20the%20active%20form%20of%20the%20molecule%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Corey%20L.%20Hartman%2C%20MD%2C%20a%20board-certified%20dermatologist%20and%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fskinwellness.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESkin%20Wellness%20Dermatology%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226e4accb9-48d5-4a17-9ba9-5666cfc82a72%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20retinol%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetinol%20is%20a%20natural%20form%20of%20vitamin%20A%20that%20you%20can%20find%20over%20the%20counter%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-retinol-cream%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretinol%20creams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20serums%2C%20moisturizers%2C%20under-eye%20products%2C%20and%20body%20lotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20well%20tolerated%20by%20most%20patients%20and%20is%20a%20great%20starting%20point%20for%20people%20who%20are%20new%20to%20retinoids%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Khalifian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20skin%20can%20only%20utilize%20retinoids%20in%20the%20form%20of%20retinoid%20acid.%20The%20more%20steps%20required%20for%20that%20conversion%20to%20take%20place%2C%20the%20more%20gentle%20and%20less%20irritating%20the%20product%20is%2C%20explains%20Khalifian.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20retinol%2C%20the%20conversion%20into%20retinoic%20acid%20is%20a%20two-step%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20retinol%20is%20a%20less-potent%20derivative%20of%20vitamin%20A%2C%20it%20can%20still%20be%20quite%20effective%20for%20improving%20the%20overall%20appearance%20of%20the%20skin%20with%20continued%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hartman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7ce0f20-d16d-450a-9b63-a0c75a45c514%5C%22%3ESide%20effects%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjddonline.com%2Farticles%2Fefficacy-and-tolerability-of-topical-01-stabilized-bioactive-retinol-for-photoaging-a-vehicle-controlled-integrated-analysis-S1545961624P0209X%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20very%20few%20people%20experience%20irritation%20when%20using%20retinol%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20those%20who%20do%2C%20this%20side%20effect%20is%20typically%20mild%20and%20short-lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Hartman%20says%20the%20most%20common%20side%20effects%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDryness%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERedness%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIrritation%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFlaky%20or%20peeling%20skin%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Hartman%20notes%20that%20some%20people%20may%20experience%20an%20uptick%20in%20blemishes.%20This%20is%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bpurging%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20happens%20because%20retinol%20speeds%20up%20your%20skin's%20cell%20turnover%20rate%2C%20which%20brings%20oil%2C%20impurities%2C%20and%20clogged%20pores%20to%20the%20surface%2C%20making%20them%20more%20visible.%20Fortunately%2C%20Hartman%20says%20this%20is%20almost%20always%20just%20a%20temporary%20phase%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscopeblog.stanford.edu%2F2020%2F08%2F06%2Fdoes-retinol-deserve-the-hype-a-stanford-dermatologist-weighs-in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elasting%20only%20three%20to%20four%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20most.%20Along%20with%20other%20side%20effects%2C%20the%20purging%20tends%20to%20fade%20as%20your%20skin%20adjusts%20to%20the%20retinol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20side%20effects%20are%20unbearable%2C%20though%2C%20that%20may%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20retinol%20is%20too%20strong%20for%20your%20skin%20or%20that%20you're%20using%20it%20too%20frequently.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20experts%20advise%20either%20discontinuing%20use%20and%20consulting%20your%20dermatologist%20or%20giving%20your%20skin%20a%20break%20for%20a%20week%20and%20then%20dropping%20to%20a%20lower-strength%20retinol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20worth%20mentioning%3F%20Retinol%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2F23293-retinol%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20your%20skin%20more%20sensitive%20to%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdcsnyc.com%2Fprovider%2Fbrendan-camp-md%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrendan%20Camp%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MD%2C%20a%20double%20board-certified%20dermatologist%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdcsnyc.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMDCS%20Dermatology%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20means%20you're%20more%20prone%20to%20sunburns%20while%20using%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228614864e-7821-406c-b8ab-816afdba88ee%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20Retin-A%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetin-A%2C%20the%20brand%20name%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-says-tretinoin-fixed-hyperpigmentation-and-wrinkles-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etretinoin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20a%20synthetic%20form%20of%20vitamin%20A%20that's%20available%20by%20prescription%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20product%20delivers%20the%20active%20form%20of%20retinoic%20acid%20without%20your%20skin%20having%20to%20do%20any%20fancy%20chemical%20conversions%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Khalifian.%20%26quot%3BThis%20means%20the%20product%20is%20stronger%20and%20works%20faster%20than%20over%20the%20counter%20retinol.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20quicker%20and%20more%20dramatic%20benefits%20also%20comes%20a%20downside%3A%20increased%20risk%20of%20side%20effects.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC9112391%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20research%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20most%20common%20side%20effects%20include%20peeling%2C%20itching%2C%20dryness%2C%20and%20irritation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20people%20can't%20tolerate%20tretinoin%2C%20myself%20included%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Khalifian.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20I%20advise%20my%20patients%20to%20start%20slowly%2C%20with%20a%20pea-sized%20amount%20every%20other%20night.%20If%20peeling%20or%20irritation%20occurs%2C%20you%20should%20reduce%20the%20amount%20and%20frequency%20of%20use.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20often%2C%20Retin-A%20is%20prescribed%20specifically%20to%20treat%20acne%20%E2%80%94%20including%20comedonal%20acne%20and%20inflammatory%20acne.%20It%20works%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC3225141%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelping%20to%20stimulate%20the%20growth%20of%20new%20skin%20cells%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20sloughing%20away%20old%20ones%2C%20regulating%20sebum%20production%2C%20and%20preventing%20clogged%20pores.%20It's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedlineplus.gov%2Fdruginfo%2Fmeds%2Fa682437.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacne%20to%20get%20worse%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20the%20first%20week%20or%20two%20of%20using%20this%20medication%20before%20it%20gets%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetin-A%20can%20also%20be%20prescribed%20to%20treat%20psoriasis%2C%20as%20well%20as%20address%20signs%20of%20aging%20like%20hyperpigmentation%20and%20dark%20spots%2C%20rough%20skin%2C%20and%20fine%20wrinkles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb0db6b9-f1e1-48b5-9b9b-67c276b0acf4%5C%22%3EEffects%20of%20retinol%20vs%20Retin-A%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20retinol%20and%20retin-A%20can%20be%20used%20to%20reduce%20the%20signs%20of%20aging%2C%20experts%20say%20retin-A%20is%20the%20more%20common%20choice%20for%20treating%20acne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Retin-A%20is%20much%20stronger%2C%20Hartman%20says%20you%20can%20expect%20to%20see%20more%20dramatic%20results%20and%20in%20a%20shorter%20span%20of%20time.%20When%20used%20regularly%2C%20Retin-A%20can%20yield%20skin%20improvements%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedlineplus.gov%2Fdruginfo%2Fmeds%2Fa682437.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTretinoin%2520(Altreno%252C%2520Atralin%252C%2520Avita%2Cskin%2520areas%2520and%2520unclogging%2520pores.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20little%20as%20two%20to%20three%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20although%20it%20may%20take%20up%20to%20four%20to%20six%20months.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20you%20may%20not%20notice%20improvements%20from%20over-the-counter%20retinol%20products%20until%20you've%20been%20using%20them%20regularly%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.harvard.edu%2Fstaying-healthy%2Fdo-retinoids-really-reduce-wrinkles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20least%20three%20to%20six%20months%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20shouldn't%20discourage%20anyone%20from%20using%20a%20retinol%20%E2%80%94%20anyone%20with%20sensitive%20skin%20might%20find%20it%20easier%20to%20tolerate%20a%20retinol%20product%20over%20a%20tretinoin%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Hartman.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20might%20prescribe%20a%20tretinoin%20product%20for%20patients%20with%20moderate%20to%20severe%20acne%20or%20scars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20a%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F32574009%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2020%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20women%20with%20moderate%20wrinkles%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fjocd.12131%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2015%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20women%20with%20sun-damaged%20skin%20actually%20found%20that%20the%20benefits%20of%20retinol%20are%20pretty%20comparable%20to%20tretinoin.%20When%20using%20retinol%2C%20participants%20experienced%20just%20as%20much%20of%20an%20improvement%20in%20wrinkles%2C%20discoloration%2C%20and%20pore%20size%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20only%20that%2C%20but%20they%20also%20experienced%20fewer%20adverse%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b9ebe31-767e-4f16-aea0-c46ae69f1e4e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChoosing%20the%20right%20product%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271a64c7a-4579-4f60-b51a-4147872ccd77%5C%22%3EBasic%20everyday%20skincare%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db350c5f-e7ec-4be9-bac8-4f6ae464428f%5C%22%3EAcne%2C%20wrinkles%2C%20and%20scars%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e5871387-c1a0-460c-a6c8-f6854dfaa0a1%5C%22%3EPreventing%20side%20effects%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20board%2C%20dermatologists%20agree%20the%20best%20way%20to%20reduce%20the%20potential%20side%20effects%20of%20any%20retinoids%20is%20to%20go%20low%20and%20slow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStart%20by%20using%20it%20just%20one%20to%20two%20times%20per%20week%20and%20gradually%20increase%20the%20frequency%20from%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20advises%20Hartman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20retinoids%20can%20increase%20skin%20sensitivity%20to%20the%20sun%2C%20Hartman%20also%20recommends%20using%20them%20only%20in%20your%20evening%20skincare%20routine%20and%20applying%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-sunscreen-moisturizer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esunscreen%20moisturizer%3C%2F